abstract: >
  The Derived Modular Spectrum (DMS) framework lifts modular theory from
  operators to categories and higher structures, replacing the single modular
  operator of the Modular Clifford Category (MCC) with a modular spectral
  functor that assigns modular structures to objects in a derived/infinity-
  category. From the central operator Delta_X = exp(D^2), quantum dynamics,
  spacetime geometry, gauge theory, and information-theoretic structures emerge
  through eigenvalue spectrum, modular flow, and type transitions.
